    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ranged Tactics Toolbox pg. 33</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 5</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 145</em>, <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 21</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> +50 gp <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> 20 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> B; <strong>Special</strong> performance, trip</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Ranged; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Thrown</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>This shield is designed for throwing and has specially designed straps that allow you to unclasp and throw it as a free action. Tower shields cannot be throwing shields. Neither a shield's enhancement bonus to AC nor its shield spikes apply on your attack or damage rolls. A throwing shield can't be disarmed.</p>",
